=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_FBSineN_ex6 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright gritty sound, with complex oscillator character around 51 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: gritty
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 51.1687
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.0251
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0569
  pitch_clarity: 21.3939
  inharmonicity: 0.0507
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -13.9046
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: FBSineN Example 6
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/FBSineN.html
// Tags: FBSineN, Classes, oscillator
// ---
// --- Example 6 ---
// randomly modulate params
(
{ FBSineN.ar(
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 1e4, 1e4),
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 32, 33),
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 0.5),
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 0.05, 1.05),
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 0.3, 0.3)
) * 0.2 }.play(s);
)
